The paper deals with the computational complexity of a graph operation (Seidel's switching) and its relation to the number of edges in the resulting graph. This makes it relevant to several subfields of computer science, including discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and graph theory (cs.GT).
